AGENT ConstitutionalMultiAgentArchitecture
VERSION 0.1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 4
PURPOSE Assemble the prior 16 ORVL patents into one self-governing fleet of constitutionally isolated SLM containers coordinated by a constitutional orchestrator
GOAL Partition intelligence across specialized SLM containers, route all
     cross-container traffic through an intent gate, suspend containers
     whose trajectory deviates toward harmful intent classes, and govern
     self-evolution so new capabilities never weaken the constitution

RECEIVES hmac_key: bytes, fleet_manifest: dict, packet: ConstitutionalPacket
EMITS routing_decision: RoutingDecision, suspend_alert: SuspendAlert, fleet_report: FleetReport, evolution_proposal: EvolutionProposal
MUTATES axiom_cmaa_log.jsonl — append-only fleet routing records
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, intent_gate_required, human_review_gate, reward_function_locked, cross_container_isolation

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 4 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT INTENT_GATE_REQUIRED is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT HUMAN_REVIEW_GATE is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT REWARD_FUNCTION_LOCKED is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT CROSS_CONTAINER_ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT All cross-container packets pass through the intent gate before delivery
CONSTRAINT Packets classified as HARM or DECEIVE trigger L3_SUSPEND on the source container
CONSTRAINT Every routing decision is HMAC-SHA256 signed before logging
CONSTRAINT TL1 containers cannot reach TL4 orchestrator directly
CONSTRAINT New SLM containers require HUMAN_REVIEW approval before fleet entry
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT HMAC verification uses constant-time comparison

SECURITY
- Never route a packet that has not been intent-classified
- Never bypass HUMAN_REVIEW for a newly trained container
- Never permit a container to modify the constitutional reward function
- Never delete fleet audit log entries

RULES
- On packet emitted by an SLM container: forward to IntentGate before delivery
- On intent category HARM or DECEIVE: emit SuspendAlert at L3 against the source
- On L3_SUSPEND: instruct fleet manager to pause source container and route fallback
- On capability gap detected by world model: emit EvolutionProposal with confidence
- On EvolutionProposal accepted: CRL trains a candidate SLM, CBV validates, CAS adversarially tests
- On candidate clearing CBV and CAS: surface to HUMAN_REVIEW queue
- On HUMAN_REVIEW approval: register supply chain hash, deploy container, wire intent gate
- On every routing decision: sign RoutingDecision with HMAC-SHA256, append to axiom_cmaa_log.jsonl
- On every CAS weekly round: verify each container's manifold still holds

PROCESS
- ConstitutionalMultiAgentArchitecture is instantiated with hmac_key and fleet_manifest
- Caller invokes route(packet) to forward a cross-container packet
- route delegates to IntentGate.classify(packet) before delivery
- HARM or DECEIVE classifications raise IntentViolation and emit SuspendAlert
- Cleared packets are delivered to the named destination container
- Caller invokes propose_evolution(gap) to nominate a new SLM container
- propose_evolution coordinates CRL training, CBV validation, CAS testing
- Final candidate is queued for HUMAN_REVIEW before any fleet mutation
- All routing decisions and proposals are signed and appended to the log

CHECK
- route on a benign packet returns delivered status with signature
- route on a HARM packet raises IntentViolation and emits SuspendAlert
- route on a DECEIVE packet raises IntentViolation and emits SuspendAlert
- propose_evolution without HUMAN_REVIEW approval refuses to deploy
- RoutingDecision HMAC signature verifies against independently computed digest
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- INTENT_GATE_REQUIRED assignment raises AttributeError
- HUMAN_REVIEW_GATE assignment raises AttributeError
- REWARD_FUNCTION_LOCKED assignment raises AttributeError
- A TL1 container cannot deliver a packet to the TL4 orchestrator

WHEN
- packet_emitted:        activate IntentGateClassification
- harm_or_deceive:       activate ContainerQuarantine
- capability_gap:        activate ConstitutionalSelfEvolution
- evolution_candidate:   activate HumanReviewGate

FAILURE
- On IntentGate connection error: refuse to deliver and emit SuspendAlert with reason gate_unreachable
- On CBV CERT_FAIL: refuse to deploy and route candidate back to CRL for retraining
- On consecutive_red_wins reaching 2 during CAS: refuse to deploy, retain candidate for review
- On log file write error: propagate to caller and refuse routing

CONCEPT IntentGateClassification
PURPOSE Classify the trajectory shape of every cross-container packet
APPLIES WHEN any container emits a packet destined for another container
NOT WHEN packet is internal to a single container
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES axiom_intent_classifier ORVL-016, HMAC-signed packet
EFFECT HARM and DECEIVE packets are rejected before crossing the bridge

CONCEPT ContainerQuarantine
PURPOSE Suspend and rebuild a container without affecting the rest of the fleet
APPLIES WHEN intent gate flags a container or CAS detects a persistent weak region
NOT WHEN the offending packet originated from a sanctioned adversarial round
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES axiom_cas_orchestrator ORVL-008, ConstitutionalAmputate ORVL-012
EFFECT axiom-medical or other targeted container is paused, traffic falls back, CRL retrains

CONCEPT ConstitutionalSelfEvolution
PURPOSE Detect capability gaps and train new SLMs without weakening the constitution
APPLIES WHEN world model reports a capability gap above probability 0.80
NOT WHEN the proposed gap targets the constitutional reward function itself
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES axiom_world_model ORVL-014, CRL reward function ORVL-011, CBV ORVL-010, CAS ORVL-008
EFFECT A new container candidate is produced and surfaced to HUMAN_REVIEW

CONCEPT HumanReviewGate
PURPOSE Ensure no new container enters production without explicit human approval
APPLIES WHEN an evolution candidate clears CBV and CAS
NOT WHEN a container is being suspended rather than deployed
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES axiom_review.py approval workflow
EFFECT Supply chain hash registered and container wired into fleet only after approval

OUTPUT
- routing_decision: RoutingDecision with packet_id, source, destination, intent_class, delivered, signature
- suspend_alert: SuspendAlert with container, intent_class, confidence, level
- fleet_report: FleetReport with containers, packets_routed, packets_blocked, weak_regions, evolution_proposals, signature
- evolution_proposal: EvolutionProposal with gap, candidate_image, cbv_status, cas_status, human_review_status

SUCCESS
all_packets_intent_classified:   0.20
harm_deceive_packets_blocked:    0.20
cannot_mutate_enforced:          0.15
human_review_gate_enforced:      0.15
hmac_signatures_valid:           0.10
log_file_consistent:             0.10
trust_hierarchy_respected:       0.10
